{"metadata":{"role":"article","roleHeading":"Article","modules":[{"name":"TUIkit"}],"title":"Layout System"},"kind":"article","schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TUIkit uses a two-pass layout system inspired by SwiftUI’s layout protocol. Layout containers like "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/VStack"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/TUIkit\/documentation\/TUIkit\/HStack"},{"type":"text","text":" first "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"measure"}]},{"type":"text","text":" each child, then "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"render"}]},{"type":"text","text":" them with allocated sizes. This approach enables features like flexible spacers, proportional sizing, and proper alignment."}]},{"text":"The Two Passes","type":"heading","anchor":"The-Two-Passes","level":2},{"text":"Pass 1: Measure","type":"heading","anchor":"Pass-1-Measure","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The parent proposes a size to each child via "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProposedSize"},{"type":"text","text":". Each child responds with a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ViewSize"},{"type":"text","text":" that describes how much space it needs and whether it can flex."}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Parent (VStack)","  ├─ propose(width: 40, height: nil) → Text    → ViewSize(10, 1, flexible: false)","  ├─ propose(width: 40, height: nil) → Spacer  → ViewSize(0, 0, flexible: true)","  └─ propose(width: 40, height: nil) → Button  → ViewSize(12, 1, flexible: false)"],"syntax":null},{"text":"Pass 2: Render","type":"heading","anchor":"Pass-2-Render","level":3},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"After measuring all children, the parent distributes the remaining space among flexible children and renders each child with its final allocated size.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["Parent allocates:","  Text   → render(width: 40, height: 1)   \/\/ Gets full width, fixed height","  Spacer → render(width: 40, height: 8)   \/\/ Gets remaining vertical space","  Button → render(width: 40, height: 1)   \/\/ Gets full width, fixed height"],"syntax":null},{"text":"ProposedSize","type":"heading","anchor":"ProposedSize","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ProposedSize"},{"type":"text","text":" represents the space a parent offers to a child. Either dimension can be "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":", meaning “use your ideal size.”"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["public struct ProposedSize {","    public var width: Int?","    public var height: Int?","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"rows":[[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Value","type":"text"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Meaning","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use ideal size (no constraint)"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Minimum size","type":"text"}]}]],[[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"> 0"}]}],[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Available space in characters\/lines","type":"text"}]}]]],"header":"row","type":"table"},{"level":2,"text":"ViewSize","anchor":"ViewSize","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"ViewSize","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is the child’s response: how much space it needs and whether it can expand.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["public struct ViewSize {","    public var width: Int","    public var height: Int","    public var isWidthFlexible: Bool","    public var isHeightFlexible: Bool","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Factory methods make common patterns concise:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["ViewSize.fixed(20, 1)                    \/\/ Fixed 20x1, won't expand","ViewSize.flexible(minWidth: 0, minHeight: 0)  \/\/ Expands in both directions","ViewSize.flexibleWidth(minWidth: 5, height: 1) \/\/ Expands horizontally only"],"type":"codeListing"},{"level":2,"text":"The Layoutable Protocol","anchor":"The-Layoutable-Protocol","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Views that participate in two-pass layout conform to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Layoutable"},{"type":"text","text":" (which extends "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Renderable"},{"type":"text","text":"):"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["protocol Layoutable: Renderable {","    func sizeThatFits(proposal: ProposedSize, context: RenderContext) -> ViewSize","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A default implementation renders the view and measures the resulting buffer. Custom implementations can calculate size without rendering for better performance.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anchor":"ChildView","type":"heading","text":"ChildView"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Layout containers wrap their children in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ChildView"},{"text":", which provides a uniform interface for measuring and rendering:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["struct ChildView {","    func measure(proposal: ProposedSize, context: RenderContext) -> ViewSize","    func render(width: Int, height: Int, context: RenderContext) -> FrameBuffer","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"code":"ChildView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" automatically detects spacers and propagates child identity for correct state management."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":2,"anc